  <diagram id="g0oaf5NnswbXpAvG5M7q" name="Component Diagram">
    <mxGraphModel dx="2930" dy="1887" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1920" pageHeight="1200" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="YG9WdgbKNQ_z4bUx3c4S-22" value="Version control and rollback - If the LLM generates a component that doesn&#39;t work as expected, how does the system handle reverting? You might want to consider adding a versioning mechanism in the Component/Component Metadata relationship.&#xa;Component validation - Before a generated component hits the Display Window, is there a validation/testing layer? The Chart Capability and Chat Capability in D-Agent suggest some capabilities exist, but the flow isn&#39;t explicit about quality gates.&#xa;State management - The Data Layer connects to Source, which is good, but how does state persist when components are updated? If a user has customized a dashboard and you deploy a new version of a component, what happens?&#xa;Security boundary - Where does code execution happen for LLM-generated components? If it&#39;s in the client, you&#39;ll want clear sandboxing. This could be important for the patent too - how you safely execute untrusted generated code." style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=16;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="-710" y="-1110" width="300" height="300" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
